</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udeneteth1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deneteth1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif" BORDER=0> at: 7/31/02 8:12:04 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ugegblix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gegblix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/30/02 10:02:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=79.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mighty tank wizards</span><hr size=1> I stopped meleeing while soloing at level 12 or so.  Stabbing a mob in the ass for 1 minute to save myself 40 mana never seemed to make much sense.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
The real wakeup call was when I burned a skeleton down to 5% health and then proceeded to lose 75% of my health meleeing it down the rest of the way...piercing was maxed at the time, by the way.  (The skeletons in Steamfont are quite a bit tougher than normal, btw.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
<br>
Eeps, forgot the whole point!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Just like a meleer needs to practice up their weapons skills, a good caster must practice up their spells skills...all of them.  Try to max out each spell skill every time you hit a new spell rank.  (every 4-5 levels) It REALLY sucks to get a new spell at a high level and watch it fizzle 20+ times in a row because your skill in that spell type is at 10....*cough* familiars *cough*<br>
<br>
Evocation you don't need to practice as a wizard.  That'll go up on its own.<br>
Alteration might take a bit of practice.  You want to keep it current for your evacs, roots, and ports.  Fade while inside or rooting yourself is a good way to practice.<br>
Abjuration will take some work.  It's worth keeping up for your shielding and resist lines.  Just practice with Minor Shielding.<br>
Divination needs to be kept up for Invisibility at level 16.  It's sad fizzling 40% of your mana away on a 20 mana spell.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Practice with True North.<br>
Finally Conjuration....The first useful conjure spell you receive will be at 29th.  Yikes.  If you don't practice it you'll be 150 skill points behind the curve.  There really isn't a very good spell to practice with.  Eye of Zomm and Halo of Light are probably your best bets.<br>
