<br>
You're all mad I say!  Mad!<br>
<br>
Melee is the perfect accessory for the fashionable wizard.  And, it's terribly practical. Entering combat is important for our profession for a few simple reasons.<br>
<br>
The most important reason I find for jumping into the fray is to get that defense and dodge up fast. While when solo or in small groups we're big on the offensive punch, when in a full group we're really a heavily defensive profession.<br>
<br>
Evacuation is obviously our fotre and and important skill set.  But evacing isn't only based on our abilty to cast.  No one evacs when the fight is easy and nice.  You evac when some idiot tank pulls 37 red mobs to your camp.  To get that spell off we need to be dodging attacks, and having our AC bolstered with a good defensive skill gives us the time to click our heals 3 times and get the heck out of there.<br>
<br>
Gaining agro is something we're VERY good at, and it's often our responsibilty as well.  When some crazy thing starts chewing on your enchanter or your cleric and they need some room to save everyone else, we're there to get said critters attention.  A quick nuke and 30 clicks of the agro stick and we're now enemy #1.  We've got to be able to survive the attention while the 'chanter casts their mezz however, and good defensive melee skills give us that opportunity.<br>
<br>
On a more offensive note, I find never needing to mem' &quot;finishing nukes&quot; a great asset.  At the end of any kite session I'm not plinking the wounded prey with a low nuke.  I jump right up,  stab it a few times, and it dies. Not only does this save me mana but it gives me a free spell slot to utilize any way I like.  And free spell slots are the greatest gift of all.<br>
<br>
I could list the way my melee skills have kept me alie in duels with other casters, but I don't want to give away all my tank-fu secrets.<br>
<br>
So I say melee, and melee hard.  Get those skills up and someday when you loot that staff that procs Ice Comet, you're going to be a foe worth fighting.<br>
<br>
(And yes, since we wizards have a good chance of scoring a critical proc, we can actualy melee for more than any tank class...)<br>
<br>
-Ephelba Westwitch<br>
54th Channeler of the League of Shadows<br>
Tanking Goddess<br>
