<br>
You could also overburn to draw agro, but that's risky as you can often bite off more than you can chew, so to speak.<br>
<br>
You will do absolutly no appreciable damage swinging a weapon in combat...none.  You'll do an order of magnitude more damage in the same period of time by simply casting one DD and medding back the mana.  If you want to work your defensive skills, use root and throw a few pokes in while you're taking a few hits, but I really wouldn't spend any amount of time specifically trying to get any single weapon skill up...let alone all of them.<br>
<br>
BTW, if you do want to improve your defensive skills, try to get an agility buff first.  Agility increases the rate at which you learn defensive skills like defense, dodge, etc.  Dexterity increases the rate at which you learn offensive melee skills like weapon skills.  The higher of Intelligence or Wisdom helps you learn pretty much every other type of skill. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udeneteth1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deneteth1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Seeker of Truth</span><br>  Posts: 330<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/12/02 12:43:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=79.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://deneteth.freeservers.com/image/den2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tank Grrrl</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Gaining agro is something we're VERY good at, and it's often our responsibilty as well<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
