<br>
Proximity seems to be directly tied to how well our spells land, at least latter on in levels.  And the closer we get the less we're resisted. <br>
<br>
So, when I decide to run up to whatever it is we're killing so I don't waste mana on a resist message, I arm my weapon du jour and attack. And, suprisingly enough, I often hit. Am I dishing out the same damage as the melees with my weapon?  No, not usualy. But I can land a nice lil hit, and when I proc an effect I can add quite a bit of damage to my nuke. No casters is unhappy to see 30 or 50 points added to their spell damage.<br>
<br>
Sure, it's not the straw that breaks the Sleeper's back, but any damage addition is a good addition.<br>
<br>
-Ephelba <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udeneteth1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deneteth1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Seeker of Truth</span><br>  Posts: 338<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/20/02 5:43:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=79.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://deneteth.freeservers.com/image/den2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Melee Mayhem</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Proximity seems to be directly tied to how well our spells land, at least latter on in levels. And the closer we get the less we're resisted. <br>
