<br>
But being in melee range is not a reason to melee <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=stavehamvaliant>StavehamValiant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/4/02 8:44:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=79.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mighty tank wizards</span><hr size=1> I say keep on fighting. Even after 18 when you get the evac spell, even after you get past 29. In fact, if you can, always fight. Around 33 you will either be close to or have maxed out your melee skills. Keep upgrading your weapons as you can. And don't listen to anyone who says you have to stop meleeing. <br>
<br>
There are some advantages to this. First, a maxed out defense is free ac. So take that free ac. A maxed out dodge can save you from a few hits. Take that to. Less damage means longer life. Getting hit less means better chances to get off a spell if you do get mobbed. <br>
<br>
I usually run in assist the tank with melee. Once I know that the damage I will do with a spell won't aggro the thing on me, I hit it with a spell. <br>
<br>
And if any tanks are reading this, Tanks that switch targets before it's dead, this is not helping. All it does is leave the mob alive and pissed at the next person who hits it hard. Usually a caster, so don't complain when you have to pull a mob off a caster. <br>
<br>
The other advantage of being up close to the fighting is that if something does aggro on you, the fighters are right there to try and help get it off you. The worst thing you can do is run around going HELP, HELP. Has this ever worked? Has a mob ever said, Oh he is running away, well I'll hit this fighter, he's closer. No the mob gets to attack your rear end, you don't even get a stab or bash in. running around makes the Mob harder for anyone else to target and hit. Which means they can't do enough damage to pull aggro. Your gonna take some damage if you run away or just stand there. So why not make it easier for someone to have a chance to save your but? What if you run out of range of a heal? Then you have no one to blame but yourself. <br>
<br>
Right now I'm 35. Recently I was in a group with an Enchanter. Who kept harassing me about meleeing. That Wizards shouldn't melee after 29, there was no point, that I'm not even going to hit the mobs, that I was going to get everyone killed messing around and so on. <br>
<br>
First, I was hitting the mobs, and with a shaded dagger, I was doing 12 to 22 damage per hit. Which is a lot for a caster (and if I can get a better weapon I will). and once the mob was two thirds down I hit it was a level 29 fire spell and finished it off. During the whole time I never got past 50% mana used. Meanwhile, this enchanter who claimed to be an expert on Wizards was casting Clarity on the Monk in the group, along with Intellectual Advancement. When asked about this, he claimed that when he got to the room join the group, there was fighting going on and he just started buffing people. Even so, what good is Clarity to even  a caster in the middle of a fight? Your not going to get any mana back of a significate amount to make a difference. <br>
<br>
You can be a melee wizard after 29, you just have to learn when to melee and when not to. When it's six against one mob, I'm not going to waste mana blasting a dark blue mob when we can cut it down in less then 30 seconds and it has been snared. Now when it's 3 or more mobs, the magic starts flying. When it's over 5 mobs, I change tactics again and pull mobs (unless there is an enchanter around) way from the main fighting and root tthem. (try and find the weakest mob to pull away, since your root spell has a better chance of sticking).<br>
<br>
People often say mana=life for casters. If you believe this, melee is a good way to help take a mob down and use less mana. I always say, any damage is better then no damage. Outside of the above mentioned &quot;expert&quot; enchanter, people can be shocked when I melee, but pleased when I do so and amazed that I hit for so much (for an caster that is).<br>
<br>
So if you want to tank and be a melee caster your whole life, go for it. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=stavehamvaliant>StavehamValiant</A> at: 9/4/02 8:51:39 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ututmosisnakptah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tutmosis Nak Ptah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/4/02 5:11:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=79.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mighty tank wizards</span><hr size=1> Hmm, Just my 2cp worth here. Melee all you want, it will get you a lot of laughs when fighting higher level mobs. Just last night I struck a Phase Spider in the Dragon Necropolis and I hit it for 12dmg !! that alone was enough to send the group into a fit of laughter. Of course I swung at the thing 7 times before I landed that blow.<br>
<br>
StavehamValiant, With all due respect your melee will get you killed at higher levels. The first time the mob goes into a rampage or a frenzy it will be time to rez the melee wizzy. If that is the risk you wish to take for 12dmg then by all means carry on. But you will be failing your group with your death as you will not be there when things go bad.<br>
<br>
